div.p: Figure: The layout in memory of the collection of toys. The "m_pToys" attribute (a) is a pointer that stores the address of an array of "n" pointers (b). Each element of the array is a pointer to an object of type "Toy" (c). Both "ShoppingCart" and "ConfirmationOrder" classes will create the array (b) dynamically; that is a resource that both classes will have to manage.

ul.li: The "ShoppingCart" will (dynamically) create copies of the toys that the client provides (c); these are also resources that the class must manage.
The "ConfirmationOrder" will store the addresses of the toys that the client provides (c); no copies are made. The "Toy" objects will be managed by the client.
